WEBVTT

00:01.600 --> 00:03.090
Previously on Elementary...
How did you come to hear
of me, Ms. Wen?

00:03.130 --> 00:04.358
I knew your brother, Mycroft.

00:04.400 --> 00:06.095
You don't like me
very much, do you?

00:06.140 --> 00:07.767
I don't have to like you,
I just have to help you.

00:07.800 --> 00:11.258
Before my stepfather adopted me,
I was Joan Yun.

00:12.840 --> 00:15.434
Why don't you just admit
you're my half sister?

00:18.280 --> 00:20.248
Running away
won't work.

00:20.280 --> 00:22.248
I'm a detective,
I'll just find you again.

00:22.290 --> 00:23.689
I've got nothing
to say to you.

00:23.720 --> 00:24.687
Okay, Sherlock and I
just helped you out

00:24.720 --> 00:26.517
with a really big problem;
the least you could do

00:26.560 --> 00:28.118
is tell me how long
you've known I exist.

00:28.160 --> 00:29.479
Two years.

00:29.530 --> 00:32.090
But you never called me,
you never came to see me.

00:32.130 --> 00:34.758
Because I never wanted to have
this conversation With you.

00:34.800 --> 00:36.563
It wouldn't have been
this conversation.

00:36.600 --> 00:38.659
It would have been, "Hi, Joan,
I'm Lin, I'm your half sister."

00:38.700 --> 00:40.668
You want to know
more about me? ﬁne.

00:40.700 --> 00:42.668
My mom came to the U.S. in 1980.

00:42.710 --> 00:44.405
She met your dad,
got knocked up.

00:44.440 --> 00:47.079
For a few years, he held it
together, we were a family,

00:47.110 --> 00:50.102
and then one day out of the
blue, he takes apart our TV,

00:50.150 --> 00:51.708
says it's sending messages
that could hurt us.

00:53.620 --> 00:55.815
He went off his meds.
Mom didn't understand.

00:55.850 --> 00:57.408
She didn't know anything
about schizophrenia.

00:57.450 --> 00:59.418
She hardly spoke English.

00:59.460 --> 01:01.485
A few days before
he abandoned us,

01:01.520 --> 01:03.078
he told her about
his first family,

01:03.130 --> 01:04.529
you, your brother, your mom.

01:05.860 --> 01:07.657
That must have been
hard for her.

01:07.700 --> 01:10.294
The hard part was having
to raise me by herself.

01:10.330 --> 01:11.695
The stuff he said
before he left,

01:11.730 --> 01:13.163
that could have been
more ranting.

01:13.200 --> 01:14.531
That's why she didn't
tell me about it

01:14.570 --> 01:18.165
until she had a health scare
a couple years ago.

01:18.210 --> 01:20.178
I searched your names
on the Internet,

01:20.210 --> 01:21.609
"Joan," "Oren," "Mary,"

01:21.640 --> 01:23.198
then I dug a little deeper,

01:23.250 --> 01:24.205
found out you worked
for the police

01:24.250 --> 01:25.649
with a guy named Sherlock,

01:25.680 --> 01:26.840
and he had a brother
who had just died.

01:26.880 --> 01:29.815
Why didn't you just come
and see me then?

01:29.850 --> 01:32.819
Because I realized I already had
all the family I needed.

01:32.860 --> 01:35.715
I only came to you for help
because I was desperate.

01:35.760 --> 01:38.786
But, hey, now you've
got the whole story.

01:38.830 --> 01:42.197
So why don't you do
what I always intended to do--

01:42.230 --> 01:44.198
pretend you never heard it,

01:44.230 --> 01:46.198
forget all about your
crazy-ass dad's other family.

01:46.240 --> 01:48.196
What if that's not what I want?

01:48.240 --> 01:49.207
It doesn't
matter.

01:49.240 --> 01:51.708
It's what I want.

01:57.910 --> 02:01.175
(workout music plays)

02:07.420 --> 02:09.752
(beeping)

02:19.500 --> 02:21.866
*

02:50.570 --> 02:51.969
(car chirps)

02:52.000 --> 02:54.195
(car alarm sounds)

02:59.380 --> 03:01.439
*

03:07.520 --> 03:09.579
BELL: Time of death is
a little before 4:00 am.

03:09.620 --> 03:10.985
Victim is Phoebe Elliot.

03:11.020 --> 03:12.817
She was an assistant
at a marketing fIrm

03:12.860 --> 03:14.452
that does a lot
of business with Asia,

03:14.490 --> 03:17.459
so she would work late,
then hit the gym.

03:17.490 --> 03:19.890
She used rideshare apps
like 20055 to get around.

03:19.930 --> 03:24.219
So Ms. Elliot summoned a 20055
car to pick her up around 3:45.

03:24.270 --> 03:26.238
Gym's door camera doesn't
cover the street,

03:26.270 --> 03:28.238
but it does show
her leaving the gym

03:28.270 --> 03:31.637
when her driver, Sharif,
was about two minutes out.

03:31.670 --> 03:33.535
He arrived and found her body.

03:38.010 --> 03:40.319
She was shot
from this direction.

03:40.350 --> 03:42.511
Blood splatter that way.

03:42.550 --> 03:44.939
There's a void to the right.

03:44.990 --> 03:47.208
Where's the missing blood?

03:49.460 --> 03:51.428
Probably on the shooter's car.

03:51.460 --> 03:53.325
You saying this was a drive-by?

03:53.360 --> 03:55.294
Not so much a drive-by,
more like a parked-by.

03:55.330 --> 03:57.298
Car approaches from this way,

03:57.330 --> 03:58.922
she mistakes it
for her rideshare,

03:58.970 --> 04:02.406
approaches the car
only to be gunned down.

04:02.440 --> 04:04.829
And the car departs
with her blood

04:04.870 --> 04:07.873
on the inside
of the passenger door.

04:10.410 --> 04:11.877
Does she look familiar
to you guys?

04:11.910 --> 04:13.377
No. Why?
I don't know.

04:13.420 --> 04:15.911
I could swear I've seen her
somewhere before.

04:15.950 --> 04:18.919
Most drive-bys, the perps
don't use their own car,

04:18.950 --> 04:19.951
they steal one.

04:21.360 --> 04:22.884
What's your point?

04:22.930 --> 04:25.057
When we were poking around
for next of kin this morning,

04:25.090 --> 04:28.457
all that turned up
was a brother, Keith.

04:28.500 --> 04:31.424
Just did a two-year stint
for grand larceny auto.

04:33.370 --> 04:35.429
MAN: I've been living
with Phoebe since I got out.

04:35.470 --> 04:38.064
She was helping me get
my life together.

04:38.110 --> 04:40.476
She means...

04:40.510 --> 04:42.444
She meant everything to me.

04:42.480 --> 04:44.448
Listen, two days ago,

04:44.480 --> 04:46.072
one of your neighbors
called in a noise complaint.

04:46.110 --> 04:47.771
She wouldn't give her name,

04:47.820 --> 04:49.549
just said she could hear
you and your sister arguing.

04:49.590 --> 04:52.309
I don't remember
fighting two days ago.

04:52.360 --> 04:54.316
But you and your sister
did fight.

04:54.360 --> 04:55.315
No.

04:55.360 --> 04:56.554
I mean, yeah.

04:56.590 --> 04:57.557
You know, sometimes.

04:57.590 --> 04:59.399
It was rough.

04:59.430 --> 05:00.590
Moving in with her.

05:00.630 --> 05:02.564
She... she had all these rules.

05:02.600 --> 05:03.999
Was one of them, "Don't shoot me

05:04.030 --> 05:05.861
whilst pretending
to be my rideshare"?

05:05.900 --> 05:08.437
BELL:
Her phone is missing.

05:08.470 --> 05:10.438
We're pretty sure it was taken
by whoever shot her.

05:10.470 --> 05:13.678
Maybe you sent her some texts
you didn't want us to see.

05:13.710 --> 05:16.679
I will do whatever you want
to prove I didn't do this.

05:16.710 --> 05:19.076
You want me to take
a polygraph? No problem.

05:19.110 --> 05:20.919
Want me to give you
a sample of my DNA?

05:20.950 --> 05:22.918
I will do whatever it takes.

05:22.950 --> 05:24.918
Just please rule me out

05:24.950 --> 05:27.089
so you can find the person
that really killed Phoebe.

05:27.120 --> 05:29.088
All right, say we believe you.

05:29.120 --> 05:32.453
Can you think of anyone else
who had reason to kill Phoebe?

05:32.500 --> 05:35.389
Maybe a stalker?
Stalker?

05:35.430 --> 05:37.660
She was getting a lot
of attention lately.

05:37.700 --> 05:39.497
Something about a selfie she
took when she was in college.

05:39.540 --> 05:42.759
That's where I knew her from.

05:42.810 --> 05:44.664
She was in the culture section
of the Dispatch.

05:44.710 --> 05:47.372
How does a selfie
make her newsworthy?

05:47.410 --> 05:51.779
Ephraim Hill is an appropriation
artist from Portland.

05:51.810 --> 05:54.415
He pulls images
from social media

05:56.650 --> 05:58.686
His _show has been
touring the country,

05:58.720 --> 06:01.154
but this is his first
time in New York.

06:01.190 --> 06:03.624
His work has been
getting a lot of buzz.

06:03.660 --> 06:06.629
So this guy rips off
other people's selfies,

06:06.660 --> 06:08.025
blows them up,

06:08.060 --> 06:10.028
and then charges a
hundred grand apiece?

06:10.070 --> 06:12.459
I'm surprised we're not
investigating his murder.

06:12.500 --> 06:14.866
The rise of social
media has created

06:14.900 --> 06:16.868
a generation
of narcissists

06:16.910 --> 06:20.505
eager to offer up their private
images for public consumption.

06:20.540 --> 06:22.701
But like peacocks
spreading their tails,

06:22.750 --> 06:25.139
such displays,
whilst feeding self-esteem,

06:25.180 --> 06:28.377
also risk attracting
the attention of predators.

06:30.190 --> 06:32.988
You think Keith Elliot
was on to something?

06:33.020 --> 06:35.113
Someone saw her picture
here, got obsessed?

06:35.160 --> 06:36.957
It's one
possibility,

06:36.990 --> 06:39.129
but_ some of the women whose
Images have been stolen

06:39.160 --> 06:41.526
have been
very upset.

06:42.670 --> 06:44.422
Some have threatened to sue.

06:44.470 --> 06:45.664
Maybe Phoebe was one of them.

06:45.700 --> 06:47.668
Ah, it's
about time.

06:47.700 --> 06:49.065
What's about time?

06:49.100 --> 06:50.909
My assistant called
the police yesterday.

06:52.240 --> 06:54.208
I'm Ephraim Hill.

06:54.240 --> 06:56.800
You are here about
a break-In, are you not?

06:56.850 --> 06:58.806
No. There was a
burglary here?

06:58.850 --> 07:01.819
Do you see any art
in these empty spaces?

07:01.850 --> 07:05.217
One might argue there's no art
in the occupied spaces either.

07:05.250 --> 07:06.808
One might.

07:06.860 --> 07:08.452
In fact, I'd welcome it.

07:08.490 --> 07:09.889
See, argument creates awareness,

07:09.930 --> 07:12.592
and awareness drives sales,
but two nights ago,

07:12.630 --> 07:15.224
someone broke in and stole
five of my portraits.

07:15.260 --> 07:18.821
Tragic as that must be,
we're here about Phoebe Elliot.

07:18.870 --> 07:20.462
We were wondering how she felt

07:20.500 --> 07:22.536
about being included
in your exhibit.

07:22.570 --> 07:24.162
Well, why?

07:24.210 --> 07:27.236
She was murdered
just before 4:00 am.

07:27.280 --> 07:28.633
We'd show you the crime
scene photographs,

07:28.680 --> 07:30.500
but you'd probably just
recontextualize them.

07:30.550 --> 07:33.519
Oh, my God.

07:33.550 --> 07:35.677
And, what, you're here
because you think that I...?

07:35.720 --> 07:38.541
A lot of the women were not
happy about becoming your muses.

07:38.590 --> 07:41.514
No, but Phoebe wasn't like that.
She was flattered.

07:41.560 --> 07:43.858
She reached out through
my agent to say so.

07:43.890 --> 07:46.188
She even did some personal
appearances here.

07:46.230 --> 07:48.596
You mind telling us where you
were around 4:00 this morning?

07:48.630 --> 07:49.995
EPHRAIM:
I was on a plane.

07:50.030 --> 07:51.827
Coming home from Paris.

07:51.870 --> 07:54.134
That's where I was when I
learned about the burglary.

07:55.670 --> 07:56.932
Do you think
there's a connection?

07:56.970 --> 07:58.767
The timing is curious,
let's just leave it at that.

07:58.810 --> 08:00.209
No, you don't understand.

08:00.240 --> 08:03.277
If the same person
committed both crimes,

08:03.310 --> 08:05.278
if someone had a problem
with me and Phoebe,

08:05.310 --> 08:08.518
I think I might know who it is.

08:08.550 --> 08:11.542
You are not an artist.

08:11.590 --> 08:13.558
You are a misogynistic phony.

08:13.590 --> 08:17.651
And all the little fangirls
who support you are just as bad.

08:17.690 --> 08:21.023
But when you stole my image,
you messed with the wrong woman.

08:21.060 --> 08:23.028
You all deserve what's coming.

08:23.070 --> 08:25.698
So you can understand why we
wanted to speak with you.

08:25.730 --> 08:28.528
Can you tell us where you were
the past two nights

08:28.570 --> 08:30.629
between midnight and 6:00 am?

08:30.670 --> 08:32.638
I was here, sleeping.

08:32.680 --> 08:34.875
You sounded pretty serious
about getting revenge

08:34.910 --> 08:36.878
against Ephraim Hill
and women like Phoebe.

08:36.910 --> 08:39.640
I did, didn't I?
(chuckles)

08:39.680 --> 08:44.083
I'm working on a part
for this Off-Off-Broadway show.

08:44.120 --> 08:46.918
She's an anarchist,
like, really angry.

08:46.960 --> 08:49.758
But it's a character;
I would never kill anyone.

08:49.790 --> 08:51.052
I'm a vegan.

08:51.090 --> 08:54.059
HOLMES:
So when you threatened revenge,

08:54.100 --> 08:55.658
what exactly did
you have in mind?

08:55.700 --> 08:58.589
Here, I'll show you.

09:09.340 --> 09:11.877
These are portraits
from Ephraim's exhibit.

09:11.910 --> 09:15.311
I put on a wig and went
into the gallery one day.

09:15.350 --> 09:18.217
I used _a hidden camera and took
pictures of his pictures

09:18.250 --> 09:20.218
of our pictures.

09:20.260 --> 09:21.750
I was gonna sell them
outside the showroom

09:21.790 --> 09:23.678
for 50 bucks apiece.

09:23.730 --> 09:25.686
Undercut him and give him
the finger at the same time.

09:25.730 --> 09:28.722
That video was just a part
of my marketing campaign.

09:28.760 --> 09:30.728
When did you take
this picture?

09:30.770 --> 09:33.364
Couple weeks ago.

09:33.400 --> 09:36.904
This man at the edge
of the frame...

09:36.940 --> 09:38.760
he is not in the portrait
at the gallery.

09:40.410 --> 09:43.208
Additionally,
that canvas has folds

09:43.250 --> 09:45.741
angled away from the corners.

09:45.780 --> 09:47.111
In this version,
they're parallel.

09:47.150 --> 09:49.118
So that would mean that
this portrait in the gallery

09:49.150 --> 09:51.948
is not the same one
that was there two weeks ago.

09:51.990 --> 09:53.787
I think someone replaced it
with a forgery.

10:01.130 --> 10:04.725
This just arrived from, uh, CSU.

10:04.770 --> 10:06.738
Mr. Hill conﬁrmed
it is a fake.

10:06.770 --> 10:08.738
And he agrees the only time
it could have been switched

10:08.770 --> 10:10.738
was during the burglary.

10:10.770 --> 10:13.933
So the thief didn't steal
five portraits, he stole six.

10:13.980 --> 10:16.949
Why just swap one
out with a forgery?

10:16.980 --> 10:19.244
I think the burglary
was a mere diversion.

10:19.280 --> 10:21.646
Switching Phoebe's portrait
was the true goal.

10:21.680 --> 10:23.682
Light's better
in the study.

10:27.190 --> 10:29.158
(Holmes grunts)

10:29.190 --> 10:32.796
Speaking of distractions,

10:32.830 --> 10:36.391
couldn't help but notice
a few on your part today.

10:36.430 --> 10:37.761
Anything amiss?

10:37.800 --> 10:38.994
(exhales)

10:39.030 --> 10:40.895
No, I'm fine.

10:40.940 --> 10:44.262
You're drinking out of the bowl
we use for Clyde's baths.

10:47.780 --> 10:50.146
(sighs)

10:50.180 --> 10:51.704
I went to see Lin yesterday.

10:51.750 --> 10:53.012
Lin Wen?

10:53.050 --> 10:54.677
Her case was resolved,
was it not?

10:54.720 --> 10:55.641
Yes, but...

10:55.680 --> 10:57.079
Are you still irked
that she and my brother

10:57.120 --> 10:58.314
once rode below the crupper?

10:58.350 --> 10:59.783
Did you think he was a virgin?

10:59.820 --> 11:02.015
She isn't Mycroft's ex-lover.

11:02.060 --> 11:03.755
She isn't his ex-anything.

11:04.960 --> 11:06.029
She's my sister.

11:10.230 --> 11:12.733
While your half-blood sibling
might have deceived,

11:12.770 --> 11:14.692
exploited and then spurned you,

11:14.740 --> 11:16.332
I might suggest
that the final outcome

11:16.370 --> 11:19.032
is not as tragic
as you make it out to be.

11:19.070 --> 11:20.833
She never wants to see me again.

11:20.880 --> 11:22.745
My brother enlisted the NSA

11:22.780 --> 11:24.748
to fake his own death
two years ago.

11:24.780 --> 11:26.008
You don't see me complaining.

11:26.050 --> 11:27.779
Well, that's different.

11:27.820 --> 11:30.015
I mean, you and Mycroft,
you had each other growing up.

11:30.050 --> 11:32.109
I mean, for better
or for worse.

11:32.150 --> 11:34.948
But she is a missing... piece.

11:34.990 --> 11:36.252
And she's not
the only one.

11:36.290 --> 11:37.826
Your father.

11:37.860 --> 11:39.487
I mean, I always thought
that he left us

11:39.530 --> 11:41.191
because he was sick.

11:41.230 --> 11:42.925
He wasn't capable
of being

11:42.970 --> 11:44.824
mﬂwahmm

11:44.870 --> 11:45.894
But he was capable.

11:45.930 --> 11:47.295
Just not with us.

11:48.870 --> 11:50.508
It sounds like he got better
and then...

11:50.540 --> 11:52.872
stayed with Lin
and her mother for years.

11:52.910 --> 11:55.128
So I guess what
I want to know is

11:55.180 --> 11:56.738
how could he
be a father

11:56.780 --> 11:58.202
to someone else--

11:58.250 --> 12:00.445
even for a little while--

12:00.480 --> 12:02.448
but not even try
with me and Oren?

12:04.090 --> 12:06.786
But I'm not gonna beg.

12:06.820 --> 12:08.811
I left her mother a message.

12:10.390 --> 12:12.790
If Lin won't speak to me,
maybe she will.

12:12.830 --> 12:14.991
(phone chimes)

12:20.340 --> 12:22.831
Marcus _has uncovered a rather
interesting piece of information

12:22.870 --> 12:24.462
about our erased man.

12:24.510 --> 12:26.034
I'm now quite certain

12:26.070 --> 12:27.469
that Phoebe's killer

12:27.510 --> 12:29.137
and the burglar
are one and the same.

12:29.180 --> 12:31.068
Why?

12:31.110 --> 12:34.079
It appears that
both crimes were committed

12:34.120 --> 12:37.089
to protect the perpetrator
of a third crime.

12:38.590 --> 12:41.855
As we know,

12:41.890 --> 12:43.551
this man

12:43.590 --> 12:46.024
was excised
from the forgery

12:46.060 --> 12:47.493
left hanging in
Ephraim Hill's gallery.

12:47.530 --> 12:49.896
But that wasn't
the only alteration.

12:49.930 --> 12:51.864
Phoebe's selfie
captures the man

12:51.900 --> 12:53.561
exiting this car.

12:53.600 --> 12:54.999
The car would've been
too difficult

12:55.040 --> 12:56.860
to remove unnoticed,

12:56.910 --> 12:59.435
so instead, the forger
altered the license plate,

12:59.470 --> 13:02.109
changing this "3" to an "8."

13:02.140 --> 13:03.903
We ran the correct number.

13:03.950 --> 13:05.178
And?

13:05.210 --> 13:06.814
The car once belonged

13:06.850 --> 13:08.875
to a Louis Bowman,

13:08.920 --> 13:10.478
presumably our erased man.

13:10.520 --> 13:12.340
Mr. Bowman is currently serving

13:12.390 --> 13:14.517
a life sentence for murder.

13:14.560 --> 13:16.289
I suspect that the burglary

13:16.320 --> 13:17.981
and Phoebe's execution

13:18.030 --> 13:20.521
were committed to keep
Louis Bowman

13:20.560 --> 13:22.528
in prison.

13:22.560 --> 13:23.959
Because this picture,

13:24.000 --> 13:26.025
Phoebe's original selﬁe,

13:26.070 --> 13:28.231
may well prove
that Louis Bowman is innocent.

13:34.910 --> 13:36.969
Three years ago, Marissa Kagan,

13:37.010 --> 13:38.898
a student at North
Connecticut Univer5ity,

13:38.950 --> 13:40.872
_ was shot and killed
in her off-campus apartment.

13:40.920 --> 13:42.842
A fellow student,
Louis Bowman,

13:42.890 --> 13:44.289
was convicted
of her murder.

13:44.320 --> 13:46.982
He said he was
at the campus library

13:47.020 --> 13:48.282
when Marissa
was killed,

13:48.320 --> 13:49.514
but no one could
corroborate his alibi.

13:49.560 --> 13:50.879
Until now.

13:50.930 --> 13:53.148
Our current murder victim,
Phoebe Elliot,

13:53.200 --> 13:55.919
took this selfie
in 2013.

13:56.900 --> 13:58.868
This is the campus
library behind her,

13:58.900 --> 14:00.299
and based on
the clothing

14:00.340 --> 14:01.989
