25:59.720 --> 26:01.017
WATSON:
We've studied your record.

26:01.060 --> 26:02.982
You're very fast.

26:03.020 --> 26:04.681
And you've had an unusually
high rate of results

26:04.730 --> 26:06.357
that support the State.

26:06.390 --> 26:08.221
I'm good at my job.

26:08.260 --> 26:09.818
But we don't think you
actually do your job at all.

26:09.860 --> 26:12.090
We think you rely
on "dry-labbing."

26:12.130 --> 26:13.688
You write false reports.

26:13.740 --> 26:15.594
Which conform to the wishes
of the authorities,

26:15.640 --> 26:17.835
instead of actually testing
the samples that you're given.

26:17.870 --> 26:19.701
BELL: It's not like this kind
of thing hasn't happened before.

26:19.740 --> 26:22.777
They've had the same problem
in Massachusetts,

26:22.810 --> 26:24.744
North Carolina;
even the FBI's lab

26:24.780 --> 26:26.338
has made thousands
of questionable hair matches

26:26.380 --> 26:28.848
over the last 20 years,
including 32

26:28.880 --> 26:30.279
in death penalty cases.
HOLMES: Mm-hmm.

26:30.320 --> 26:31.685
Sometimes it's
inexpenence.

26:31.720 --> 26:32.880
_ Sometimes it's
just incompetence,

26:32.920 --> 26:34.683
but you-- you're
a supervisor.

26:34.720 --> 26:36.381
I think you know
what you're doing.

26:36.420 --> 26:38.752
So perhaps you're just driven
by a desire to feel important,

26:38.790 --> 26:40.655
to be the hero,
to be the key witness

26:40.700 --> 26:42.349
putting bad guys away--
am I right?

26:42.400 --> 26:43.924
I have an excellent reputation.

26:43.970 --> 26:46.268
Ask anyone-- I am an asset
to law enforcement.

26:46.300 --> 26:48.666
Yes, but you're not supposed
to be an asset, are you?

26:48.700 --> 26:50.099
You're supposed
to be a scientist.

26:50.140 --> 26:52.734
You're supposed to be an
impartial seeker of truth.

26:52.770 --> 26:54.635
But you're not,
you're a charlatan!

26:54.680 --> 26:56.671
And you've sent at least
one innocent man to prison--

26:56.710 --> 26:57.642
Louis Bowman!

26:57.680 --> 26:59.807
I stand by my work.

26:59.850 --> 27:01.715
BELL: Then you won't
mind if we retest

27:01.750 --> 27:03.411
all the evidence in
the Phoebe Elliot case

27:03.450 --> 27:05.281
at another facility?

27:05.320 --> 27:07.185
Because if we're right
about what's going on here,

27:07.220 --> 27:10.155
the person who had the best
motive to kill her was you.

27:11.930 --> 27:14.296
You're police.

27:14.330 --> 27:15.957
You know how things work.

27:16.000 --> 27:18.321
In most cases,
even high profile ones,

27:18.370 --> 27:20.691
detectives figure out
who did it

27:20.740 --> 27:23.664
by talking to the right people,
following their gut.

27:23.710 --> 27:26.861
It's finding proof
that's tough.

27:26.910 --> 27:28.775
You used to be able
to get conVIctions

27:28.810 --> 27:31.074
wit_h witness statements
or Circumstantial eVIdence,

27:31.110 --> 27:33.169
but these days

27:33.210 --> 27:35.314
juries want
something physical.

27:35.350 --> 27:36.840
They want DNA.

27:36.880 --> 27:39.747
And you give it to them.

27:39.790 --> 27:41.815
I'm on your side.

27:41.860 --> 27:44.158
You know that DNA
can be more subjective

27:44.190 --> 27:46.021
than people think.

27:46.060 --> 27:47.755
It can be hard to find
an uncontaminated sample.

27:47.800 --> 27:50.360
The results _
can be inconcluswe.

27:50.400 --> 27:52.163
So when the police
are sure who did it,

27:52.200 --> 27:54.737
but the tests aren't clear,

27:54.770 --> 27:58.706
I give law enforcement
the benefit of the doubt.

27:58.740 --> 27:59.934
You frame people.

27:59.970 --> 28:03.178
You corrupt the justice process
from the inside.

28:03.210 --> 28:05.940
I help get convictions.

28:05.980 --> 28:07.948
Louis Bowman got
a life sentence thanks to you.

28:07.980 --> 28:09.470
Only it's looking
more and more

28:09.520 --> 28:12.444
like he didn't kill
Marissa Kagan three years ago.

28:12.490 --> 28:15.254
GREGSON: We think that when
Phoebe Elliot realized she had

28:15.290 --> 28:17.155
a picture that could
exonerate him,

28:17.190 --> 28:18.487
she told someone.

28:18.530 --> 28:19.986
Maybe it was you.

28:20.030 --> 28:21.793
Maybe it was the lab to confirm

28:21.830 --> 28:23.149
whether the DNA was accurate.

28:23.200 --> 28:25.828
HOLMES:
If that was the case,

28:25.870 --> 28:27.326
you would've realized
how much was at stake.

28:27.370 --> 28:29.930
An audit would uncover the
same pattern that we found.

28:29.970 --> 28:31.858
You were in danger
of going to jail.

28:31.910 --> 28:33.366
And having every conviction

28:33.410 --> 28:36.277
that you'd engineered
overturned.

28:36.310 --> 28:38.005
Killing Phoebe would
stop that from happening.

28:38.050 --> 28:40.143
I told you I didn't do that.

28:40.180 --> 28:41.818
I never even met the woman.

28:41.850 --> 28:44.045
Phoebe was shot
in the Bronx.

28:44.090 --> 28:45.785
But her killer drove a car

28:45.820 --> 28:47.310
full of evidence all
the way to Bridgeport.

28:47.350 --> 28:49.113
And the only reason to do that

28:49.160 --> 28:50.855
was to make sure that
that car was processed

28:50.890 --> 28:53.222
at the Connecticut
forensics lab-- your lab--

28:53.260 --> 28:55.455
where you could implicate
whoever you wanted.

28:55.500 --> 28:58.298
Phoebe's brother was the
lowest hanging fruit.

28:58.330 --> 29:00.321
HOLMES:
You said yourself
good police work

29:00.370 --> 29:01.860
usually reveals the killer.

29:01.900 --> 29:03.936
In this case,
you have means and motive.

29:03.970 --> 29:05.460
And unless you can
provide us with an alibi,

29:05.510 --> 29:07.239
you also have opportunity.

29:07.270 --> 29:08.976
I was home alone that night.

29:09.010 --> 29:11.069
But I can prove
I didn't kill her.

29:11.110 --> 29:12.873
Recheck the DNA evidence
from the stolen car

29:12.910 --> 29:14.377
in your own lab.

29:14.420 --> 29:15.773
Or a private lab.

29:15.820 --> 29:17.378
Or any lab you want.

29:17.420 --> 29:19.547
You'll see that none of it
belongs to me.

29:19.590 --> 29:20.955
What would that prove?

29:20.990 --> 29:22.309
You're an expert.

29:22.360 --> 29:23.987
You could've
removed your DNA.

29:24.030 --> 29:25.554
Or worn protective gear
to make sure

29:25.590 --> 29:27.922
it never ended up in that car
in the first place.

29:27.960 --> 29:30.963
I could've removed all the DNA
from that car, sure.

29:31.000 --> 29:35.835
But to remove only my own,
that would be a neat trick.

29:35.870 --> 29:37.565
As far as protective gear goes,

29:37.600 --> 29:40.307
why would I risk
getting pulled over

29:40.340 --> 29:42.831
for driving around
in a Hazmat suit?

29:42.880 --> 29:44.802
In your version
of the story,

29:44.850 --> 29:46.875
I knew that I'd be
processing the evidence,

29:46.910 --> 29:49.845
so I wouldn't have needed
to keep my DNA out of the car,

29:49.880 --> 29:52.815
because I never would've
reported a match to myself.

29:52.850 --> 29:54.351
Right?

29:54.390 --> 29:56.950
I didn't kill anyone.

29:56.990 --> 29:58.480
Do the tests.

29:58.530 --> 30:00.122
Do them right.

30:00.160 --> 30:02.958
You'll see I'm innocent.

30:07.870 --> 30:09.360
Every piece of evidence
she ever handled,

30:09.400 --> 30:11.834
every lab report
with her name on it,

30:11.870 --> 30:13.462
it's all got to be reexamined,

30:13.510 --> 30:15.603
which means hundreds of cases

30:15.640 --> 30:17.278
getting reopened
in Connecticut.

30:17.310 --> 30:18.948
Of course, in the meantime,
we got our own problems.

30:18.980 --> 30:20.948
I'm not convinced that
she killed Phoebe Elliot.

30:20.980 --> 30:22.311
Nor am I.

30:22.350 --> 30:23.988
You have to appreciate
the irony.

30:24.020 --> 30:25.942
Were someone like Ms. Mercado
to process the eVIdence

30:25.990 --> 30:27.446
they would happily provide

30:27.490 --> 30:28.957
the false match
needed for a conviction,

30:28.990 --> 30:30.878
but_ an honest test would
likely exonerate her.

30:30.930 --> 30:35.026
Still, whoever killed Phoebe had
to have known about her, right?

30:35.060 --> 30:37.028
Why else would they drive the
car all the way to Connecticut?

30:37.060 --> 30:39.062
They were counting on her
doing what she did.

30:39.100 --> 30:40.965
They knew that no matter
what the test revealed,

30:41.000 --> 30:43.639
her report would confirm
the police's initial suspect.

30:43.670 --> 30:45.934
Her ability to produce
evidence on demand

30:45.970 --> 30:47.369
can't have gone
completely unnoticed

30:47.410 --> 30:49.878
by Connecticut's entire
criminal justice system.

30:49.910 --> 30:51.639
Which means we're probably

30:51.680 --> 30:54.012
looking for someone
in law enforcement.

30:56.420 --> 30:58.980
(knocking)

31:10.500 --> 31:11.922
Could we talk?

31:11.970 --> 31:13.961
(door closes)

31:16.100 --> 31:17.567
More detective stuff?

31:17.600 --> 31:18.931
A technician's been
falsifying evidence

31:18.970 --> 31:20.460
at a crime lab.

31:20.510 --> 31:22.569
We think someone knew
and took advantage.

31:22.610 --> 31:24.009
I was going through
all of her cases

31:24.050 --> 31:25.005
and making lists
of the people

31:25.050 --> 31:26.574
who were in the habit

31:26.610 --> 31:28.612
of steering work her way.

31:28.650 --> 31:31.585
No Sherlock?

31:31.620 --> 31:33.542
He's talking to a suspect
we already know about.

31:38.060 --> 31:40.654
I don't do this very often,
so I may suck at it,

31:40.690 --> 31:42.658
but I came to apologize.

31:42.700 --> 31:47.091
Obviously, I have a lot of
unresolved anger over my father.

31:47.130 --> 31:50.099
Our father.

31:50.140 --> 31:53.007
I lied when I said he hated you.

31:53.040 --> 31:55.429
He never came back to us,
and as far as I know,

31:55.480 --> 31:57.300
he never even knew
your mom remarried.

31:57.340 --> 32:00.138
So I'm sorry.

32:03.020 --> 32:07.081
Well, I had a feeling
that you... might get angry

32:07.120 --> 32:09.088
after you found out
that I called your mother,

32:09.120 --> 32:10.712
so I'm sorry, too.

32:10.760 --> 32:13.126
I've never really been good
at taking no for an answer.

32:13.160 --> 32:16.550
(chuckles) Pretty sure
that's a Yun family trait.

32:16.600 --> 32:17.965
Not knowing when to quit.

32:18.000 --> 32:20.969
When in doubt, charge ahead.

32:23.070 --> 32:25.436
You have the right
to be curious about Dad.

32:25.470 --> 32:28.268
Like you said,
for you, he's a mystery.

32:28.310 --> 32:30.528
But for me...

32:30.580 --> 32:32.741
I remember him giving
me piggyback rides

32:32.780 --> 32:34.975
and calling me
silly nicknames.

32:35.020 --> 32:37.215
And I remember him getting
angry and confused,

32:37.250 --> 32:39.616
and then he was gone.

32:39.650 --> 32:41.618
He was someone
that I had and I lost,

32:41.660 --> 32:45.448
and it hurts
to think about that.

32:45.490 --> 32:49.096
Aanay, um, I talked to Mom,

32:49.130 --> 32:52.019
and she said it's okay
if you want to call her again.

32:57.140 --> 32:59.131
I appreciate that.

33:03.110 --> 33:05.169
Good luck with all this.

33:15.090 --> 33:17.251
I already told you I
didn't have anything to do

33:17.290 --> 33:19.679
with Marissa's case
three years ago.

33:19.730 --> 33:21.357
That's not exactly
true, is it?

33:21.400 --> 33:23.550
By now, you've heard
about the arrest

33:23.600 --> 33:26.023
of the crime
lab superwsor

33:26.070 --> 33:28.038
who processed the evidence
in Marissa's murder.

33:28.070 --> 33:29.662
It turns out that you made
quite a few calls to her

33:29.700 --> 33:30.735
while she was working the case.

33:30.770 --> 33:32.806
So?

33:32.840 --> 33:34.808
So your cousin Bailey Neal
is in Narcotics.

33:34.840 --> 33:37.570
Over the last few years, he's
sent a lot of cases Zoe's way.

33:37.610 --> 33:41.341
Maybe that's just a coincidence,
or maybe he knew how she worked.

33:41.380 --> 33:43.177
Maybe he told you
about his secret weapon.

33:43.220 --> 33:44.585
Okay.

33:44.620 --> 33:46.588
First, that's BS.

33:46.620 --> 33:49.282
Bailey is a good cop, the best.

33:51.130 --> 33:54.190
Second, the only reason
I called Zoe as much as I did

33:54.230 --> 33:56.198
was because I felt guilty.

33:56.230 --> 33:58.095
About?

33:58.130 --> 34:00.291
Marissa was my friend.

34:00.330 --> 34:03.128
If I didn't drop out,
I don't know,

34:03.170 --> 34:05.638
maybe Louis wouldn't have
stopped obsessing over me

34:05.670 --> 34:07.206
and started obsessing over her.

34:07.240 --> 34:09.538
So did I encourage Zoe

34:09.580 --> 34:11.844
to make sure_he_wouldn't
get away With it? Yes.

34:11.880 --> 34:15.111
Absolutely. But I was like that
with everyone on the case.

34:15.150 --> 34:17.118
Well, there could be another
reason that you wanted

34:17.150 --> 34:19.186
to point Zoe at Louis.

34:20.320 --> 34:22.117
You killed Marissa.

34:22.160 --> 34:24.185
What?

34:24.230 --> 34:26.186
You say that you and Louis
weren't a couple.

34:26.230 --> 34:27.379
He says that you were.

34:27.430 --> 34:28.829
What if he's telling the truth?

34:28.860 --> 34:31.124
He grew interested
in your friend.

34:31.170 --> 34:32.489
You got jealous.

34:32.530 --> 34:34.862
(chuckles)
Something funny?

34:34.900 --> 34:39.166
Yeah. Uh, Marissa and I never
would have fought over a guy.

34:39.210 --> 34:40.199
You were that close?

34:40.240 --> 34:42.105
No, she was that gay.

34:43.380 --> 34:45.348
Her family is super religious.

34:45.380 --> 34:47.348
She never got around
to telling them.

34:47.380 --> 34:50.349
The only people who knew
were me and Phoebe

34:50.380 --> 34:52.189
and a couple of other friends.

34:52.220 --> 34:53.209
I'll give you their names.

34:53.250 --> 34:54.217
You can talk to them.

34:54.260 --> 34:55.318
They'll tell you.

34:55.360 --> 34:57.316
After she was killed,

34:57.360 --> 34:59.726
we decided it wasn't
our place to say anything.

34:59.760 --> 35:02.194
Plus we knew it wasn't relevant

35:02.230 --> 35:04.824
because we knew Louis
was the one who did it.

35:04.870 --> 35:06.667
Let's say we believe you.

35:06.700 --> 35:08.497
Is there any other
"irrelevant" information

35:08.540 --> 35:09.598
you've been keeping to yourself?

35:11.470 --> 35:14.200
You say Louis is innocent,
I say you're wrong,

35:14.240 --> 35:18.506
but Marissa was seeing somebody,
a married woman.

35:18.550 --> 35:20.677
She never told me who,

35:20.710 --> 35:24.180
but she did say she was
pushing her to get a divorce.

35:32.230 --> 35:33.629
WATSON: How'd it go
with Amanda Neal?

35:33.660 --> 35:35.252
I don't believe
she's our killer.

35:35.300 --> 35:37.427
How's it going with the
case files of Zoe Mercado?

35:37.460 --> 35:38.825
Well, from the looks of things,

35:38.870 --> 35:40.269
there were at least
a few dozen people

35:40.300 --> 35:41.665
in Connecticut law enforcement

35:41.700 --> 35:43.497
who knew what
she was up to.

35:43.540 --> 35:45.508
They'd either specifically
request her to process evidence,

35:45.540 --> 35:48.930
or they would ask her to repeat
a test done by a subordinate

35:48.980 --> 35:50.470
to get a better result.

35:50.510 --> 35:52.307
You already know who we're
looking for, don't you?

35:52.350 --> 35:54.318
As a matter of fact,
I believe I do.

35:54.350 --> 35:56.511
That's nice.

35:56.550 --> 35:58.211
I got there 20 minutes ago.

36:08.500 --> 36:09.899
Can I help you?

36:09.930 --> 36:11.898
I'm Detective Bell
with the NYPD.

36:11.930 --> 36:13.898
This is Detective Gould
with the Avon PD.

36:13.930 --> 36:16.899
Does Assistant District Attorney
Christa Pullman live here?

36:16.940 --> 36:19.204
She's my wife.
Is everything okay?

36:19.240 --> 36:20.400
She's fine.

36:20.440 --> 36:21.805
My colleagues
and I are here

36:21.840 --> 36:23.979
about a college student
named Marissa Kagan.

36:24.010 --> 36:25.978
Does that name
ring a bell?

36:26.010 --> 36:28.274
It was tragic,
what happened to her.

36:28.320 --> 36:30.242
Actually, that's what
we're here to talk about.

36:30.280 --> 36:31.884
The kids are at school.

36:31.920 --> 36:33.182
Come in.

36:36.460 --> 36:38.428
I don't understand.

36:38.460 --> 36:40.826
Marissa's murder
was solved years ago.

36:40.860 --> 36:43.420
It was that stalker, that boy
she went to school with.

36:43.460 --> 36:45.826
We now think
Louis Bowman was framed

36:45.870 --> 36:47.667
and that the person
who did it

36:47.700 --> 36:50.396
also recently shot and killed
a young woman in the Bronx.

36:50.440 --> 36:53.261
That's horrible.

36:53.310 --> 36:55.335
But shouldn't you be talking
to Christa about this?

36:55.380 --> 36:56.608
She'll be home in a few hours.

36:56.640 --> 36:58.005
WATSON:
We will.

36:58.040 --> 37:00.008
We've recently become
aware of a suspect

37:00.050 --> 37:02.018
that the police never pursued,

37:02.050 --> 37:04.689
a married woman with whom
Marissa was havmg an affair.

37:06.450 --> 37:08.850
A witness reports seeing
Marissa's lover wearing

37:08.890 --> 37:11.620
a very distinctive
green-and-white Baja sweater.

37:13.030 --> 37:14.349
Any idea who that might be?

37:16.360 --> 37:18.328
Christa has a sweater like that.

37:18.370 --> 37:20.497
Did you know
about the affair?

37:20.530 --> 37:22.669
I found out.

37:22.700 --> 37:24.839
BELL:
Your wife's failure to disclose

37:24.870 --> 37:26.667
her relationship
to the victim at trial

37:26.710 --> 37:28.871
is gonna be enough for
Avon PD to get a warrant.

37:28.910 --> 37:32.277
Someone's gonna be here shortly
to collect samples of her DNA.

37:32.310 --> 37:34.312
Her toothbrush,
her hairbrush should do.

37:37.420 --> 37:39.411
They can take
whatever they need.

37:40.420 --> 37:42.513
But first...

37:42.560 --> 37:44.926
there's something else
you should know.

37:46.660 --> 37:48.628
My personal attorney
is on her way over.

37:48.660 --> 37:51.390
I'm not going to discuss any
of this until she gets here.

37:51.430 --> 37:52.795
That's all right.

37:52.830 --> 37:54.798
We don't really need
to ask any questions.

37:54.840 --> 37:56.694
Your wife already
confessed to everything.

37:56.740 --> 37:58.708
What?
GREGSON: Please.

37:58.740 --> 37:59.729
Sit.

38:06.650 --> 38:09.619
We know that you and Marissa
were having an affair

38:09.650 --> 38:12.448
and that your wife,
Teri, found out.

38:12.490 --> 38:16.017
She confront_ed_ Marissa
over your infidelity,

38:16.060 --> 38:19.427
and that confrontation ended
in Marissa's murder.

38:19.460 --> 38:21.621
WATSON: When Teri got home,
she told you what she had done.

38:21.660 --> 38:23.025
She was ready to face
the consequences

38:23.060 --> 38:25.665
and turn herself in,
but you told her not to,

38:25.700 --> 38:27.327
that you would
take care of everything.

38:27.370 --> 38:30.692
GREGSON: And you did,
you made sure that Zoe Mercado

38:30.740 --> 38:35.109
was the one who tested
the saliva on Marissa's body,

38:35.140 --> 38:38.576
and, like you expected,
she matched it to Louis Bowman.

38:38.610 --> 38:40.498
You thought that was
the end of it.

38:40.550 --> 38:43.917
But then, a few weeks ago,
Phoebe Elliot contacted you.

38:43.950 --> 38:46.646
She told you what she'd seen
in that blown-up selfie

38:46.690 --> 38:48.453
in Ephraim Hill's gallery.

38:48.490 --> 38:50.708
She said it seemed to
corroborate Bowman's alibi.

38:50.760 --> 38:53.581
HOLMES:
You shared this with your wife,

38:53.630 --> 38:55.598
and according to her,
you once again promised

38:55.630 --> 38:57.598
to "handle" everything.

38:57.630 --> 38:59.598
You tried to convince Phoebe,
as you did me,

38:59.630 --> 39:01.598
that the photograph
wasn't reliable.

39:01.640 --> 39:05.667
When that failed, Teri says she
took matters into her own hands.

39:05.710 --> 39:07.359
First, you replaced Phoebe's
selfie with a forgery.

39:07.410 --> 39:08.832
Then, the next night,

39:08.880 --> 39:10.734
she went to a restaurant
near your home in Avon

39:10.780 --> 39:12.941
and stole a car
out of the valet lot.

39:12.980 --> 39:14.948
Then she drove to Phoebe's
gym in the Bronx,

39:14.980 --> 39:17.619
waited for her and shot her.

39:17.650 --> 39:19.743
GREGSON: We've got a signed
confession from your wife

39:19.790 --> 39:22.156
admitting to the burglary at
the gallery and to the murders

39:22.190 --> 39:25.751
of Marissa Kagan
and Phoebe Elliot.

39:25.790 --> 39:27.758
No.

39:27.790 --> 39:29.758
No, you coerced this.

39:29.800 --> 39:31.859
I can get this thrown out.

39:31.900 --> 39:34.494
Your wife's confession
was entirely voluntary.

39:34.540 --> 39:37.532
We've got it in writing
and on tape.

39:37.570 --> 39:39.765
There was a time when that would
have been the end of the matter,

39:39.810 --> 39:42.529
but ex-lab supervisor
Zoe Mercado is right

39:42.580 --> 39:45.777
about one thing: juries do not
like to convict these days

39:45.810 --> 39:48.472
without DNA evidence,
so we retested

39:48.520 --> 39:51.148
the saliva found on Marissa's
shirt three years ago

39:51.180 --> 39:52.613
just to be certain.

39:52.650 --> 39:54.515
It's a preliminary
match for Teri.

39:54.560 --> 39:55.879
GREGSON: There isn't much doubt
she killed Marissa,

39:55.920 --> 39:57.717
but Phoebe Elliot?

39:57.760 --> 39:59.489
That's another story.

39:59.530 --> 40:01.794
BELL:
We compared Teri's DNA

40:01.830 --> 40:04.867
to skin cells recovered from
the car used in Phoebe's murder.

40:06.730 --> 40:10.530
If ex-lab supervisor Zoe Mercado
or anyone of her ilk

40:10.570 --> 40:12.561
had performed those tests,

40:12.610 --> 40:14.202
they would have rightly
come back a match.

40:14.240 --> 40:16.208
But in this case,
we didn't inform the lab

40:16.240 --> 40:18.447
which DNA belonged
to our suspect.

40:18.480 --> 40:21.449
We provided several samples
from your home,

40:21.480 --> 40:24.688
samples from other suspects,
like Keith Elliot, Ephraim Hill.

40:24.720 --> 40:26.085
Even threw in a sample
from my tortoise

40:26.120 --> 40:27.712
just to keep them on their toes.

40:27.750 --> 40:29.718
And imagine our surprise
when the lab revealed

40:29.760 --> 40:33.025
that the DNA in the car
didn't belong to your wife,

40:33.060 --> 40:35.551
it belonged to you.

40:35.600 --> 40:38.569
You knew Phoebe's
brother had a record.

40:38.600 --> 40:40.568
With his history,
it was a matter of time

40:40.600 --> 40:41.999
before we zeroed in on him.

40:42.040 --> 40:44.838
And with a little nudge,
Zoe would attribute

40:44.870 --> 40:47.839
any physical evidence found
to him and not you.

40:47.870 --> 40:52.239
WATSON: Teri felt responsible
for the whole chain of events.

40:52.280 --> 40:54.669
So to protect you
and to leave your children

40:54.720 --> 40:56.711
with at least one parent
not in prison,

40:56.750 --> 40:59.514
she tried to take
the blame for both crimes.

40:59.550 --> 41:01.518
Fortunately for them,

41:01.560 --> 41:04.017
we understand they have
very loving grandparents.

41:04.060 --> 41:07.188
Unfortunately for you,

41:07.230 --> 41:09.198
when lab work is done right,

41:09.230 --> 41:12.199
without bias,
without assumption,

41:12.230 --> 41:15.529
it really does tend to convince
a jury of a killer's guilt.

41:18.000 --> 41:19.604
LIN:
This is gonna sell quickly,

41:19.640 --> 41:21.039
_ so let me know
if you're interested.

41:28.650 --> 41:30.641
Looking for a place of your own?

41:30.680 --> 41:32.682
Can't beat the location.

41:32.720 --> 41:35.689
Your office said you'd be here.

41:35.720 --> 41:40.521
I called your mother today,
and we spoke for a while.

41:40.560 --> 41:42.596
Your Mandarin must be good.

41:42.630 --> 41:44.291
No, she seems nice.

41:44.330 --> 41:46.662
She's the best.

41:46.700 --> 41:47.962
She invited me to tea.

41:48.000 --> 41:49.888
I'm not surprised.

41:49.940 --> 41:52.602
I took a rain check.

41:52.640 --> 41:55.609
Look, I know this
has been a lot for you.

41:55.640 --> 41:58.609
It's been a lot for me, too.

41:58.650 --> 42:01.619
And I just thought,
"Why rush it?"

42:01.650 --> 42:06.314
I'll have tea with your mother
when you're ready to join us.

42:06.350 --> 42:08.580
Why?

42:10.620 --> 42:12.588
Because you're my sister.

